class Solution {
    public int minInsertions(String s) {
        int res = 0, cnt = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == '(') {
                cnt++;
            } else {
                cnt--;
                if (cnt < 0) {
                    res++;
                    cnt++;
                }
            }
        }
        return res + cnt;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the string once, counting the number of opening parentheses and the net number of closing parentheses. The minimum number of insertions is the sum of the number of closing parentheses that don't have a matching opening parenthesis and the net number of opening parentheses.

